From: Mauri de Souza Meneguzzo <mauri870@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath12k: disable PCIe ASPM L1 states on shutdown

The WCN7850 (Qualcomm FastConnect 7800) enters a PCIe ASPM L1 power
state after ath12k_pci_power_down() restores ASPM and issues a soft
reset during shutdown. On subsequent warm reboots the BIOS cannot
enumerate the device because the PCIe link remains in L1, requiring a
full power drain (PSU disconnect) to recover.

Disable all L1 ASPM states in the shutdown handler after the device is
powered down so the link stays active through the reboot cycle and the
BIOS can enumerate the device on the next boot.

---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/pci.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/pci.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/pci.c
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/pci.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/pci.c
@@ -1744,6 +1744,11 @@ static void ath12k_pci_shutdown(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 
 	ath12k_pci_set_irq_affinity_hint(ab_pci, NULL);
 	ath12k_pci_hw_group_power_down(ab->ag);
+	pci_disable_link_state(pdev, PCIE_LINK_STATE_L1 |
+			       PCIE_LINK_STATE_L1_1 |
+			       PCIE_LINK_STATE_L1_2 |
+			       PCIE_LINK_STATE_L1_1_PCIPM |
+			       PCIE_LINK_STATE_L1_2_PCIPM);
 }
 
 static __maybe_unused int ath12k_pci_pm_suspend(struct device *dev)
